SIMPLE: rifling
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rifling
<hw>Ri"fling</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The act
or process of making the grooves in a rifled cannon or gun barrel.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>The system of grooves in a rifled gun barrel or
cannon.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Shunt rifling</b></col>, <cd>rifling for cannon, in which
one side of the groove is made deeper than the other, to facilitate
loading with shot having projections which enter by the deeper part of
the grooves.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rift</ent>⟦br⟧
